DIGEST
SB 330 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Owen
Present law provides an automated speed enforcement device or mobile speed camera that
is used to issue a citation by mail can only be used by local municipal authorities or local
parish authorities upon entrance to each school zone, where there shall be painted a two-
foot-wide yellow stripe completely across the roadway with "Entering School Zone" painted
in twelve-inch white lettering visible.
Proposed law changes the provision from a painted two- foot-wide yellow stripe completely
across the roadway with "Entering School Zone" painted in twelve-inch white lettering
visible at the entrance of a school zone to the word "SCHOOL" proportionately striped
across the lane adjacent to the S1-1 school sign and white lettering at the entrance to any
school zone equipped with automated speed enforcement devices, in accordance with the
current edition of the Manual on Uniform Traffic Control Devices.
Present law provides for a painted, two-foot-wide yellow stripe completely across the
roadway with "School Zone Ahead" painted in 12 inch white lettering. Proposed law repeals
present law.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 32:47(A)(4); repeals R.S. 32:47(A)(5))
